Bless you baby girl, from all mums around the world.

I'm don't think this is right at all. I do hope this individual receives justice but we can't assume that it's a hate crime just cause she's transgender. We have to treat those who receive a sex change the same as everyone else. Everyone who is murdered isn't murder out of hate. A lot of times it's pure ignorance or anger for a particular reason, besides gender or race or sexual preference. I only say this because when we build on the idea that this was pure hate we stir up our own emotions to prepare us to rise up unnecessarily based on our own assumptions of what we believe happened base on stereotype and thus we turn what we believe into what we """"want"""" to believe
